				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText"> Charm kiting XP (which method is best)<a name="68600"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 1 04 2:03 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Greetings,
<br />

<br />
I must say that I've read quite a few of the posts and guides and have learned a lot.  There is one thing I still haven't been able to locate (I'm sure it's here though)
<br />

<br />
So lets say I'm in PoN Charm kiting the stalkers.  I grab my pet, let it get beat on and I invis at 5% health or so to break charm.
<br />

<br />
I have a number of options now.
<br />

<br />
I can grab a new pet and send it after the one at 5% and let it kill it all by itself.
<br />

<br />
I can dot the 5% stalker, then grab a new pet and send it after it.
<br />

<br />
Does one method or the other produce better XP per kill?
<br />

<br />
Would I get more XP if I chant kited the 5% stalker and just send my new pet after another target?
<br />

<br />
I sort of prefer to just get one killed, less aggro overall on me<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  but I'm open for better technique.
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance!</span></td>
