				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re:  Charm kiting XP (which method is best)<a name="68717"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 1 04 9:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You need to do SOME damage to get the xps.  ALL the damage is not necessary.  If there is and XP difference its nominal.  But I still suggest you go ahead and chant the ex-pet down.  This is less for xps than it is for control.
<br />

<br />
My &quot;pet attack&quot; key is as follows:
<br />
line 1&gt; /pet attack
<br />
line 2&gt; /pet target
<br />

<br />
With the above hotkey, I send the pet in and immediately retarget my pet.  Then the &quot;toggle-last-2-targets&quot; key goes between my pet and what I sicked him on.  I chant down the ex-pet and toggle then charm.  This way, the most injured and most aggro mob is consistantly my new pet.  I very seldom get one that own't stay in the fight in preference to bashing my skull in. This is what I mean by control.
<br />

<br />
I generally toggle to the soon-to-be-new-pet when the ex-pet has enough chants stuck on him that he will die before they all wear off.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
