			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re:  Charm kiting XP (which method is best)<a name="68737"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 2 04 3:30 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Once charm is broken, either by invis or time-out, there is a &quot;mem blur&quot; effect that occurs.  So now the damage you do to your previously charmed pet is the full 100% of it's hp, Or in the case of swarm kiting the last 5% or so of it's total hp, so you get full xp.  The trick is actually how to get faster xp.  The less hp that is left on the mob after charm breaks, the quicker you can chant it down and grab another pet, yielding faster kills, thus faster xp.  Mana regen, size of your kite, percussion mod, and mob spawn times all determine the speed.
<br />

<br />
If you use another pet to kill your previous pet, you will get less experience for the kill.  I want to say only 50%, but it may be as much as 75%.  Regardless, it is better to chant you previous pet down for full xp.  
<br />

<br />
Hope this info helps some!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
