			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re:  Charm kiting XP (which method is best)<a name="68747"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 2 04 9:02 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The only time I recharm a different pet before chanting the old 5% pet down is for survival when things have gone bad with your agro management.
<br />

<br />
A decent scenario here would be you are in a narrow hallway inside a dungeon with not much room to run from the swarm.  If there are 6 mobs on your pet, and charm breaks, it is nice to have a new pet whipping boy to take some of the heat of you.  The old pet will be on you likely, but at 5% it will not be for long, and the other 5 mobs will be on your new pet.  If there is room I try to chant the old pet down till dead then recharm a new one, but if my hps get less than 50% and the mobs are see invis type or summoners, it is a good time to allways have a pet....heh.
<br />

<br />
Lately I have never had a pet KS me so I get zero experience, yet in the past I seem to remember this happening, an easy way to test this is let a new pet kill your old 5% health pet that has been mem wiped.  You will get experience, but not as much.  I am thinking 50%.
<br />

<br />
The real tricky part to determine is at what point do you get full experience.  It is either you have done some damage and the pet does the rest, or you do 51% of the damage the pet does the rest, or you kill the mob while you have no pet.
<br />

<br />
