				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re:  Charm kiting XP (which method is best)<a name="68825"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 2 04 11:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'd really have to dig to find this in writing, but a while back they changed the way both summoned pets and charmed pets work with experience.
<br />

<br />
Summoned pets:
<br />

<br />
As long as you do 1 point of damage to the mob, you get 100% of the experience. In a group, it's the same thing. As long as SOMEONE does 1 point of damage to the mob, you will all get 100% of your alloted experience.
<br />

<br />
Charmed pets:
<br />

<br />
The experience gain is somewhat inverse to the amount of damage done by the PET. If the pet does 50% damage, YOU get 50% experience. If the pet does more then 50% but less then 75%, you get 40% I believe (can't remember exact amount now). If the pet does 100% of the damage, you get nothing.
<br />

<br />
This was a big deal to me when it first went live, as I was playing my necro a lot at the time, and before that, you had to do &gt;51% of the damage compared to SUMMONED pets to get full experience, which was a complete pain.
<br />

<br />
I have heard that DC pets are on a different table then the charmed pets even, but I can't personally confirm this. Maybe someone can troll around the chanter sites/boards to try and find some defining information.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
